<dl id="n15029a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n15" href="#n15029a">N15 (VI.D.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n15all.htm#n15029a"> 29(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ &mdash;son <sup>n</sup> / about everything</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The king suspected that this <font color="green">[despondency]</font> was because his sagas had come to an end, and he had no entertainment to offer daring the festive season. The Icelander admitted that this was really the case. &ldquo;I have only one saga left,&rdquo; he said, &ldquo;and I dare not tell that here, for it is about your own adventures in foreign lands.&rdquo; &ldquo;That is the saga I should most of all like to hear,&rdquo; said the king, and gave him directions how to make it last over the Christmas festival <small> W. A. Craige, <a name="ICEL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ICEL"><cite title="source">The Icelandic Sagas</cite></a>, (1913) 16</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c15205a" href="c15all.htm#c15205a">VI.C.15:205(a)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
